<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-11105] MetricsSystemImpl could leak memory in registered callbacks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-11105</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSystemImpl.register(final String name, final String description, final T sink)&lt;/tt&gt; method, we will also add a callback function to the &lt;tt&gt;callbacks&lt;/tt&gt; array list. However, upon unregistering, the callback function is not removed from the list in existing code. As a result, the memory allocated for the callback function could accumulate in the &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSystemImpl&lt;/tt&gt; list. In one of our cluster, we have seen a case where there are about 874 MB memory retained by &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSystemImpl&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
